                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d938">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">John T. Walsh</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 5. While Department holds that transfer of a belligerent-owned
                    merchant vessel to American purchaser made in good faith is valid, you should be
                    advised that British and French Governments have announced that they may contest
                    such transfer, particularly if the vessel shall engage in commerce with their
                    enemies or with the neutral countries contiguous thereto. Government of United
                    States does not guarantee protection in advance of the event. Question of
                    validity of transfer is one dependent upon facts of case known to parties and in
                    regard to which they can take advice of counsel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
